data-triple-N3.o: "George III (George William Frederick; 4 June 1738 29 January 1820) was King of Great Britain and King of Ireland from 25 October 1760 until the union of these two countries on 1 January 1801, after which he was King of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland until his death. He was concurrently Duke and prince-elector of Brunswick-Luneburg ("Hanover") in the Holy Roman Empire until his promotion to King of Hanover on 12 October 1814."@en
